                            <msItem>
                                <locus from="1ra" to="26vb" scheme="folios"/>
                                <title type="desc"> Proper of time</title>
                                <rubric>Feria quarta in capite <sic>ieiuvnii</sic> aske onsdag super benedictus</rubric>
                                <incipit>Cum ieiuniatis nolite fieri sicut ypocrite tristes (Matt. 6:16)</incipit>
                                <explicit>Cecus magis ac magis clamabat ut eum dominus illuminaret Versus dirigatur collecta ut supra</explicit>
                                <note>
                                    <p> The Proper of time starts with Ash Wednesday and ends with Quadragesima Sunday.</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locusGrp>
                                            <locus from="27r" to="27v" scheme="folios"/>
                                        </locusGrp>: guidelines, but no text.</p>
                                    <p/>
                                </note>
                            </msItem>
                            <msItem>
                                <locus from="28ra" to="94vb" scheme="folios"/>
                                <title type="desc">Proper of saints</title>
                                <rubric>Hic incipit de Sanctis primo de sancto stephano antiphona</rubric>
                                <incipit>Intuens in celum beatus stephanus uidit gloriam dei </incipit>
                                <explicit>sic eius munera capiamus sempiterna gaudentes Per eundem qui theodosie virginis eodem die.</explicit>
                                <note>
                                    <p> The Proper of saints begins with St Stephen (26 Dec.) and ends with St Thomas (21 Dec.) and with the rubric for St Theodosia (18 July).</p>
                                    <p> A majority of the pages only contain the rubric for a each feast.</p>
                                    <p> Notable feasts:</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="29" to="29" scheme="folios"/> and <locus from="57r" to="57r" scheme="folios"/>: St Knud Lavard (7 Jan. and 25 June, see <bibl>
                                            <title type="short" ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/bibl/107174">Chesnutt (2003)</title>
                                            <citedRange from="77" to="78" unit="page"/>
                                        </bibl>);</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="31r" to="31r" scheme="folios"/>: St Henry (19 Jan., text not inserted);</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="34r" to="34r" scheme="folios"/>: St Ansgar (3 Feb.), concerning the text, see <bibl>
                                            <title type="short" ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/bibl/107177">Helander (1989)</title>
                                            <citedRange from="49" to="53" unit="page"/>
                                            <citedRange from="68" to="68" unit="page"/>
                                            <citedRange from="159" to="161" unit="page"/>
                                            <citedRange from="253" to="253" unit="page"/>
                                        </bibl>;</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="37r" to="37r" scheme="folios"/>: St Sigfrid (15 Feb.);</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="39v" to="39v" scheme="folios"/>: St Lucius (4 Mar.);</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="44r" to="44r" scheme="folios"/>: St Katarina of Sweden (24 Mar.);</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="51v" to="51v" scheme="folios"/>: St Halward (15 May, text not inserted);</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="52r" to="52r" scheme="folios"/>: Erik (18 May);</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="54v" to="54v" scheme="folios"/>: St Eskil (12 June);</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="55r" to="55r" scheme="folios"/>: St Vilhelm, 16 June;</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="57r" to="57r" scheme="folios"/>: St David of Munkentorp (25 June, only the rubric);</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="61v" to="61v" scheme="folios"/>: St Knud (10 July);</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="62r" to="62r" scheme="folios"/>: St Kjeld (11-18 July), regarding the antiphons, see<bibl>
                                            <title type="short" ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/bibl/107175">Gertz (1908-1912)</title>
                                            <citedRange from="279" to="280" unit="page"/>
                                            <citedRange from="283" to="283" unit="page"/>
                                        </bibl> (the antiphon for first Vespers not found in Gertz);</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="65v" to="65v" scheme="folios"/>: St Birgitta (23 July, text after the office Rosa rorans);</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="67v" to="67v" scheme="folios"/>: St Olaf (29 July);</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="74r" to="74r" scheme="folios"/>: translation of St Lucius (25 Aug.);</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="76v" to="76v" scheme="folios"/>: St Sunniva (7 Sep.) </p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="80v" to="80v" scheme="folios"/>: St Ketil (27 Sep., text not inserted);</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="82v" to="82v" scheme="folios"/>: St Birigtta (7 Oct., text after the office Birgitte matris inclite);</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="85r" to="85r" scheme="folios"/>: St Thøger (30 Oct.).</p>
                                    <p/>
                                </note>
                            </msItem>
                            <msItem>
                                <locus from="95ra" to="99va" scheme="folios"/>
                                <title type="desc">Additions</title>
                                <rubric>Eugenie uirginis</rubric>
                                <incipit>
                                    <supplied reason="omitted">M</supplied>Ortifica quesumus domine populum tuum hic in temptacionibus </incipit>
                                <explicit>vt a quibus tibi ministrantibus in celo semper assistetur ab hiis in terra vita nostra muniatur Per eum qui venturus est</explicit>
                                <note>
                                    <p/>
                                    <p>Added feasts: St Eugenia (rubric only); St Buriana ; Translation of St Birgitta; Three Maries; Patriarchs et prophets; Twenty-four elders; St Mechtild; The Lance of Lord Saviour; Crown of Thorns (rubric in Danish), St Adalbert, St Liborius; St Paulinus; St Priscus; St Edmund, St Linius?; St Saturninus (last seven saints only with a collect); St Joachim; collect for the dead; St Lupus; Feast of relics; Dedication of the church; Three Marys, one sequence, and two prayers.</p>
                                </note>
                            </msItem>
                            <msItem>
                                <locus from="99vb" to="100vb" scheme="folios"/>
                                <textLang mainLang="da" otherLangs="la"/>
                                <title type="desc">Two prayers for St Magnus</title>
                                <rubric>De sancto magno episcopo et martire Oratio</rubric>
                                <incipit>Hoffligh biscopp oc megtugh martir fattughe oc wedhertørff the menneskes myldhe patronae Sancte <sic>magus</sic>
                                </incipit>
                                <explicit>Oc with thesse thimelighe thing skulle wii forskyldhe at fanghe meth fructsommelighe gaerninghe ewyndelighethz gledhae Per christum dominum nostrum Amen</explicit>
                            </msItem>
                            <msItem>
                                <locus from="101ra" to="124ra" scheme="folios"/>
                                <textLang mainLang="da" otherLangs="la"/>
                                <title type="desc">Prayers </title>
                                <rubric>Hwo som sigh wil wærdelige redhæ ath thagæ til sigh thz werduge sacramenth tha skal han i ix daghæ til fornæ læsæ thzte som hær æffter staar <gap reason="editorial"/> ok gøræ thic læsæ so thennæ bøn</rubric>
                                <incipit>O Thw alzobarm hiertugeste gudh fadher </incipit>
                                <explicit>Thz wnnæ oss allæ samen gudh father ok søn ok then helghæ andh AmeN</explicit>
                                <note>Collection of prayers in Danish. Transcription of rubric, incipit, and explicit based on material supplied by Ingela Hedlund.</note>
                            </msItem>
